Thakuri (Nepali: ne:ठकुरी) is a caste among Nepalese peoples.
Thakuri (ठकुरी) is generally considered as one of the Pahadi (पहाडी) races in Nepal. According to the 2011 census, Thakuri population in Nepal is 425,623 (Link1). According to joshuaproject, 98.71% of Thakuri people believe in Hinduism and the majority of them speak Nepali as their first language (Link2). The majority of Thakuri people live in the mid and far western regions of Nepal. They are known for being descended from kings, and hence groups of Thakuri are sometimes called royal clans.
Thakuri in the Gandaki Zone have little Khas background.
